<p>It has been a while since my <a href="https://www.rousette.org.uk/archives/exploring-desktop-linux-p2/">last post in this series</a>. I have been pretty busy with work, but pottering with tweaking my Linux setup in the meantime. At some point, I will likely publish my dotfiles, but I am going back and forth so much on things at the moment that dotfiles would only be a transient snapshot of the way things are right now.</p>
<p>I&rsquo;m still in Hyprland, but this time I have swapped out my status bar and moved away from <a href="https://www.ml4w.com">ML4W</a> as I have added more of my own configuration. I&rsquo;ve also temporarily stepped away from Emacs while my brain adapts to switching between Linux and macOS shortcuts, and found a few new CLI apps that I really love.</p>
<h3 id="hyprland-and-friends">Hyprland and friends</h3>
<p>Playing with Hyprland continues to be great fun. I really enjoy the snappiness of it, and moving between windows, apps and workspaces with the keyboard alone is a joy. Last time, I had swapped Waybar with <a href="https://aylur.github.io/ags-docs/">ags</a> to provide a status bar. I liked it, but hit a few snags configuring it to my liking. It was nothing major, but &mdash; as I am in the exploratory phase with this at the moment &mdash; I am trying out all sorts of set-ups to see which I like best. In my wanderings, I came across <a href="https://github.com/JakeStanger/ironbar">Ironbar</a>, which (as the name hints) is written in the programming language of the hour, Rust. I managed to get it up and running quickly, and found styling and tweaking the widgets reasonably easy.</p>
<figure role="group"><img
 srcset="https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/ironbar_vivaldi.png?&w=100 100w,https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/ironbar_vivaldi.png?&w=200 200w,https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/ironbar_vivaldi.png?&w=400 400w,https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/ironbar_vivaldi.png?&w=800 800w,https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/ironbar_vivaldi.png?&w=1000 1000w,https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/ironbar_vivaldi.png?&w=1500 1500w"
